# Ship after work (Zenith Frontier)

When finishing intentional code changes for this project (implementation done, or user says เสร็จ / ship / commit / push), run the ship workflow before ending. Do **not** ship for pure Q&A, planning-only, or clearly incomplete mid-debug work.

## 1. GitHub commit + push

- Follow the repo commit protocol (status, diff, log, HEREDOC message, no secrets).
- Stage only relevant project files. Never commit `.env`, `pi-server/deploy/.pi-credentials`, keys, or credentials.
- `git push -u origin HEAD` after a successful commit.
- This project rule **overrides** the global “only commit when asked” preference for Zenith Frontier when the work turn is complete.

## 2. Cloudflare Worker (only if Worker changed)

If this turn changed anything under `worker/` (including `wrangler.toml`):

```powershell
cd worker
npx wrangler deploy
```

Skip if only frontend / docs / unrelated paths changed.

## 3. Raspberry Pi pi-server (only if Pi API changed)

If this turn changed anything under `pi-server/`:

```powershell
powershell -File pi-server/deploy/push-to-pi.ps1
```

- Deploys **only** this project’s remote dir (`PI_REMOTE_DIR` in gitignored `.pi-credentials`, typically `~/zenith-frontier-pi`).
- Do not touch other Pi projects or home folders.
- Requires SSH key `~/.ssh/zenith_pi` already authorized on the Pi.

## 4. Report

End with: commit hash/URL, whether Worker deploy ran, whether Pi deploy ran (or skipped + why).
